The paper deals with the problem of decoding in communication systems with imperfect channel estimation, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The paper also considers the use of nearest neighbor decoders, which is a topic in coding theory and signal processing (cs.SY). The paper discusses the use of Gaussian codebooks, which is a topic in modulation and coding (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of bit interleaved coded modulation (BICM), which is a topic in networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
